Material Information Summary – Buru Energy ASX Announcement (17 July 2025)

Key Updates on Rafael Gas Project:

  • Revised development timeline:
  • Drilling sequence changed – Rafael B well to be drilled and tested first, followed by recompletion of Rafael 1.
  • Drilling now expected June Quarter 2026 (previously planned earlier).
  • Final Investment Decision (FID) delayed to early Q3 2026 (shifted by ~6 months).

  • First production target unchanged – late 2027.

  • Reason for change:

  • Risk mitigation – Rafael 1 well condition may be compromised; Rafael B expected to provide better flow test results and reserves certification.

  • Project fundamentals unchanged:

  • Still targeting feedstock supply for Rafael LNG Project (partnered with Clean Energy Fuels Australia).

  • Planning for regulatory approvals, traditional owner agreements, and gas marketing ongoing.

  • Funding/Partnering:

  • Upstream partner/funding discussions underway (data room active).

No capital raising, financial, or trading halt details disclosed.

Impact: Short-term delay in FID but no change to long-term production target. Operational risk reduced by modified drilling sequence. Partnering/funding efforts could influence capital structure.

Summary of ASX Announcement:

Company: Canadian Phosphate Ltd (ASX: CP8)
Announcement Type: Exploration Update

Material Information Extracted:

  • Exploration Target:
  • Identified phosphate (P₂O₅) target of 20.2–28.6 million tonnes at grades of 15.76%–15.96% P₂O₅.
  • Target spans ~11.5km strike length, with potential for additional 16.5km of prospective strike.

  • Based on historical drilling/trenching data (81 drillholes, 51 trenches).

  • Permit Application:

  • Submitted Multi-Year Area-Based (MYAB) Exploration Permit for 100%-owned Wapiti Phosphate Project (British Columbia, Canada).

  • Aims to advance exploration and support future Mineral Resource Estimate.

  • Key Risk Disclosure:

  • Target is conceptual; insufficient exploration to define a Mineral Resource.

Tailored for Trading/Capital Markets:

  • No capital raising or immediate financial impact disclosed.
  • Focus on resource potential and permitting progress; material for long-term valuation if exploration succeeds.

Conclusion: Operational milestone with exploration upside, but no near-term trading catalysts.

Material Information Summary:

  • Exploration Results:
  • LiDAR and SAM surveys identified a +4km VMS target corridor at the Mt Everest–Mona Mine trend.
  • High-grade copper mineralization confirmed:
    • Partial sulphides: Up to 8.19% Cu
    • Supergene mineralization: Up to 24.2% Cu
    • Gold/silver/cobalt byproducts: Up to 0.95 g/t Au, 29.1 g/t Ag, 508 ppm Co.
  • Historic mining evidence suggests untested primary sulphides below known workings.
  • New magnetic horizons identified as potential vectors for concealed VMS deposits.

Fortcoming Work:
- Follow-up rock chip sampling (focusing on Mona Mine).
- Soil sampling/mapping program to define drill targets.
- Drilling planned for untested VMS targets (no prior drilling in the area).

No material financial, capital structure, or trading-related updates identified.

Material Information Summary:

  • Significant Drill Results at RAS North:
  • MDD448: 21.7m @ 4.1 g/t Au (true width 20.3m)
  • MDD439: 25.9m @ 2.8 g/t Au (true width 23.6m)
  • MDD433: 6.4m @ 8.2 g/t Au (true width 6.0m)

  • Ongoing Drilling:

  • RAS North: Targeting further 200m northern extensions of HG1 high-grade trend.
  • RAS South: Confirming mineralization orientation for future modeling.

  • Regional Exploration (RINA): Sterilisation and infill drilling at satellite deposits (CIT, SRX, SRE).

  • Key Implication: Results likely to drive resource reclassification and enhance project economics.
